<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHANNEL ISLANDS DUO MAKE COLLEGE CHOICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRBY LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sal Tauau and Candis Carper, key components in the Channel Islands High girls' 
basketball team's drive to a share of the Marmonte League championship last 
season, have orally committed to Cal State Long Beach and Arizona State, 
respectively. 
</P>
<P>
As a junior last season Tauau, a 6-foot center, averaged 12.5 rebounds, 11.2 
assists and 2.8 assists. 
</P>
<P>
Carper, a 5-11 forward, averaged 14.2 points, 3.4 steals, 9.4 rebounds and 2.5 
blocked shots. 
</P>
<P>
Tauau, who would like to go into law enforcement, said she chose Long Beach 
over Loyola Marymount and Cal because of proximity and the school's 
criminal-justice program. She planned to sign a letter of intent today during 
the NCAA early signing period. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach was 25-9 and advanced to the second round of the NCAA Division I 
playoffs last year. 
</P>
<P>
Carper, who was recruited by 25 Division I schools, chose Arizona State on the 
basis of its pre-law undergraduate program. 
</P>
<P>
Channel Islands finished 23-7 last season and advanced to the Southern Section 
5-AA Division semifinals. KIRBY LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111490-0016 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 307494 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 14, 1990, Wednesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
