<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: K MART EMPLOYEE SHOT IN HOLDUP BY 2 GUNMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An assistant manager of a K mart store in South-Central Los Angeles was 
slightly wounded Tuesday morning when two gunmen forced their way into the 
store's vault and took an undisclosed amount of cash, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles Police Capt. Gary Brennan said the gunmen entered the store at 
Vermont and Slauson avenues when it opened at 9 a.m., overpowered two security 
guards, tied them up and ordered an assistant manager to open the store's 
vault. 
</P>
<P>
After the pair took the money, one of them fired a shot at the assistant 
manager, nicking him in the neck, Brennan said. 
</P>
<P>
Officers, believing the gunmen were still inside the store, sealed off the area 
and conducted a two-hour search, but the pair escaped, Brennan said. K mart 
officials declined comment on the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
