MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sympathy for Wood: Ron Wood, a guitarist with the Rolling Stones, was 
recovering Tuesday after breaking two legs in the aftermath of a highway 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
Wood, 43, stepped from his limousine after it crashed Monday near Newbury, in 
southern England. He was going to direct traffic away from the wreckage but an 
oncoming car hit him. Tuesday he joked with friends: "The doctors have 
prescribed as part of my treatment a pint of Guinness a day, so that can't be 
bad." One of the other drivers involved in the accident, however, said Wood had 
narrowly escaped death. BETH KLEID 
</P>
