<HEADLINE>
<P>
BODY FOUND DUMPED OFF SIDE OF ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles police were investigating the death of a man whose bludgeoned body 
was found Tuesday dumped off the side of a road in the hills above Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified body, believed to have been that of a man between 30 and 35 
years old, was found about 2 p.m. in a brushy area below the road in the 7800 
block of Mulholland Drive, Lt. Ron LaRue said. 
</P>
<P>
The man was 6 feet tall with short brown hair and mustache, and wore a red, 
short-sleeved shirt with stripes, gray shorts and white tennis shoes, Detective 
Mike Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of death was unknown but the case was being handled as a homicide. 
Coffey said the victim appeared to have been hit several times in the upper 
torso, and possibly the head, with a blunt instrument. 
</P>
<P>
"It appears that he was dragged to the edge and then pushed over the side," 
LaRue said. 
</P>
<P>
The body was 70 feet below the road on a steep hillside, wrapped in a blanket 
or sleeping bag. At least one person saw it as early as 7 a.m., Coffey said, 
"but they didn't know it was a person." 
</P>
<P>
A woman who lives in the area "got a closer look around 1 p.m." as she walked 
along the road, "thought it might be a body" and called police, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
