<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: TARPLEY TO MISS REST OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Forward Roy Tarpley will miss the rest of the Dallas Mavericks' season after 
ligament damage was discovered in his right knee Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The damage was found during arthroscopic surgery. Tarpley averaged 20 points 
and 11 rebounds in five games and was shooting 54% before he was injured during 
Friday's victory overOrlando. 
</P>
<P>
An arthroscopy also was performed on the right knee of Maverick guard Fat 
Lever. He is expected to be sidelined from four to six weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
