<P>
'LATINAS' CONFERENCE SCHEDULED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Mexican American National Women's Assn. is sponsoring a conference for high 
school girls from the Santa Ana Unified School District today at Rancho 
Santiago College. 
</P>
<P>
The title of the conference is "Latinas: Leaders of the Future," and it will 
feature speakers and exhibitors. 
</P>
<P>
About 150 girls are expected to attend. The group sponsors an "Hermanitas" or 
little sisters, program, to match professional role models with young women in 
the school system who are from low-income backgrounds or at risk of dropping 
out. 
</P>
<P>
The conference will be held from 9 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. at the college, which is 
at 17th and Bristol streets. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call Eva Lombardo at (714) 846-0997. 
