<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
SO. KOREA EXPORT CAR SALES SAG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEOUL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Korea exported 249,000 motor vehicles between January and October, down 
9.5% from a year ago, the Korea Automobile Manufacturing Assn. reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The decline in exports was attributed to price competition and sluggish demand 
in the United States, which is Korea's biggest export market. 
</P>
<P>
The association said the number of Korean-made vehicles sold on the domestic 
market in the first 10 months of this year jumped 24.8% to 768,000 from a year 
ago. Total sales rose to 748,000 cars, up 9.4% from a year ago, and 269,000 
commercial vehicles, up 29.7%. 
</P>
<P>
The officials said Hyundai Motor Co. topped the list of Korean auto makers by 
marketing 530,000 vehicles at home and abroad in the 10 months, up 7% from a 
year ago. It was followed by Kia Motors Corp. with 313,000 motor vehicles, up 
24.7%, and Daewoo Motor Co. with 135,000 vehicles, up 15.4%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
