<P>
TOWN'S GIS MAKE 'NASHVILLE NOW' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CRYSTAL SPRINGS, Miss. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Country music singer Tom T. Hall visited this town of about 5,000 to help 
comfort friends and relatives of soldiers in the 162nd Military Police Co., 
sent to Saudi Arabia last month. 
</P>
<P>
The Nashville Network's program "Nashville Now" sent Hall to the tiny community 
just south of Jackson after receiving a letter from resident Rose Beazley. 
</P>
<P>
"I just told 'Nashville Now' that a lot of our men were leaving," Beazley said, 
adding that many of the 127 soldiers, including her brother-in-law, had to 
leave young children behind. 
</P>
<P>
Hall hosted an eight-minute segment about Crystal Springs, which was broadcast 
nationally Monday on the cable network. Hundreds of people crowded into 
downtown, some waving signs and shouting messages to their soldiers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
